[section#task.promise
    [:en] Class [`task::promise_type]
    [:zh_CN] 类 [`task::promise_type]
]

[codeblock:synopsis]
namespace std::execution {
  template<class T, class Environment>
  class task<T, Environment>::promise_type {
  public:
    task get_return_object() noexcept;

    static constexpr suspend_always [[redoc("[%@lib@member initial_suspend[!task::promise_type]]")]]initial_suspend() noexcept { return {}; }
    auto final_suspend() noexcept;

    void unhandled_exception();
    coroutine_handle<> unhandled_stopped() noexcept;

    void return_void();                 // [:en] present only if [`is_void_v<T>] is [`true]; [:zh_CN] 仅当 [`is_void_v<T>] 为 [`true] 时提供；
    template<class V = T>
      void return_value(V&& value);     // [:en] present only if [`is_void_v<T>] is [`false]; [:zh_CN] 仅当 [`is_void_v<T>] 为 [`false] 时提供；

    template<class E>
      [[redoc("[=unspec]")]] yield_value(with_error<E> error);

    template<[[redoc("`:c>")]]sender Sender>
      auto await_transform(Sender&& sndr);

    [[redoc("[=unspec]")]] get_env() const noexcept;

    void* operator new(size_t size);
    template<class Alloc, class... Args>
      void* operator new(size_t size, allocator_arg_t, Alloc alloc, Args&&...);
    template<class This, class Alloc, class... Args>
      void* operator new(size_t size, const This&, allocator_arg_t, Alloc alloc, Args&&...);

    void operator delete(void* pointer, size_t size) noexcept;
  };
}
[codeblock:end]

[para]
[:en] Let [`[^prom]] be an object of [`promise_type] and let [`[^tsk]] be the
[`task] object created by [`[^prom].get_return_object()].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`[^prom]] 为 [`promise_type] 类型的对象，并令 [`[^tsk]] 为
[`[^prom].get_return_object()] 所创建的 [`task] 对象。

[:en] The description below refers to objects [`[*STATE]([^prom])],
[`[*RCVR]([^prom])], and [`[*SCHED]([^prom])] associated with [`[^tsk]]
during evaluation of [`task::[*state]<Rcvr>::start] for some receiver [`Rcvr].
[:zh_CN] 以下描述中涉及对象 [`[*STATE]([^prom])]、[`[*RCVR]([^prom])] 和
[`[*SCHED]([^prom])]，它们在针对某个接收器 [`Rcvr] 的 [`task::[*state]<Rcvr>::start]
的执行期间与 [`[^tsk]] 相关联。

[%@lib@member get_return_object[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
task get_return_object() noexcept;
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:returns]
[:en] A [`task] object whose member [*handle] is
[`coroutine_handle<promise_type>::from_promise(*this)].
[:zh_CN] 一个 [`task] 对象，其成员 [*handle] 为
[`coroutine_handle<promise_type>::from_promise(*this)]。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member final_suspend[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
auto final_suspend() noexcept;
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:returns]
[:en] An awaitable object of unspecified type ([#expr.await]) whose
member functions arrange for the completion of the asynchronous
operation associated with [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 一个未指明类型的可等待对象（[#expr.await]），其成员函数安排
与 [`[*STATE](*this)] 关联的异步操作的完成。

[:en] Let [`st] be a reference to [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`st] 为 [`[*STATE](*this)] 的引用。

[:en] The asynchronous completion first destroys the coroutine frame
using [`st.[*handle].destroy()] and then invokes:
[:zh_CN] 异步完成首先使用 [`st.[*handle].destroy()] 销毁协程帧，然后：

[list]
[item]
[:en] [`set_error(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), std::move(st.[*error]))]
if [`bool(st.[*error])] is [`true], otherwise
[:zh_CN] 如果 [`bool(st.[*error])] 为 [`true]，则调用
[`set_error(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), std::move(st.[*error]))]，否则
[item]
[:en] [`set_value(std::move(st.[*rcvr]))] if [`is_void_v<T>] is [`true], and otherwise
[:zh_CN] 如果 [`is_void_v<T>] 为 [`true]，则调用 [`set_value(std::move(st.[*rcvr]))]，否则
[item]
[:en] [`set_value(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), *std::move(st.[*result]))].
[:zh_CN] 调用 [`set_value(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), *std::move(st.[*result]))]。
[list:end]
[div:end]

[%@lib@member yield_value[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
template<class Err>
  auto yield_value(with_error<Err> err);
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:mandates]
[:en] [`std::move(err.error)] is convertible to exactly one of the
[`set_error_t] argument types of [`error_types].
[:zh_CN] [`std::move(err.error)] 可以转换为 [`error_types] 中的恰好一个 [`set_error_t] 实参类型。

[:en] Let [`[^Cerr]] be that type.
[:zh_CN] 令 [`[^Cerr]] 为该类型。

[para:returns]
[:en] An awaitable object of unspecified type ([#expr.await]) whose member
functions arrange for the calling coroutine to be suspended and then completes
the asynchronous operation associated with [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 一个未指明类型的可等待对象（[#expr.await]），其成员函数安排调用方协程的暂停，
然后完成与 [`[*STATE](*this)] 关联的异步操作。

[:en] Let [`st] be a reference to [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`st] 为 [`[*STATE](*this)] 的引用。

[:en] Then the asynchronous operation completes by first
destroying the coroutine frame using [`st.[*handle].destroy()] and then invoking
[`set_error(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), [^Cerr](std::move(err.error)))].
[:zh_CN] 则异步操作通过首先使用 [`st.[*handle].destroy()] 销毁协程帧，然后调用
[`set_error(std::move(st.[*rcvr]), [^Cerr](std::move(err.error)))] 来完成。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member await_transform[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
template<[[redoc("`:c>")]]sender Sender>
  auto await_transform(Sender&& sndr);
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:returns]
[:en] If [`[^same_as]<inline_scheduler, start_scheduler_type>] is [`true],
returns [`as_awaitable(std::forward<Sender>(sndr), *this)]; otherwise returns
[`as_awaitable(affine(std::forward<Sender>(sndr)), *this)].
[:zh_CN] 如果 [`[^same_as]<inline_scheduler, start_scheduler_type>] 为 [`true]，
则返回 [`as_awaitable(std::forward<Sender>(sndr), *this)]；否则返回
[`as_awaitable(affine(std::forward<Sender>(sndr)), *this)]。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member unhandled_exception[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
void unhandled_exception();
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:effects]
[:en] If the signature [`set_error_t(exception_ptr)] is not an element
of [`error_types], calls [`terminate()] ([#except.terminate]).
[:zh_CN] 如果签名 [`set_error_t(exception_ptr)] 不是 [`error_types] 的元素，
则调用 [`terminate()]（[#except.terminate]）。

[:en] Otherwise, stores [`current_exception()] into [`[*STATE](*this).[*error]].
[:zh_CN] 否则，将 [`current_exception()] 存储入 [`[*STATE](*this).[*error]]。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member unhandled_stopped[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
coroutine_handle<> unhandled_stopped() noexcept;
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:effects]
[:en] Completes the asynchronous operation associated with [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 完成与 [`[*STATE](*this)] 关联的异步操作。

[:en] Let [`st] be a reference to [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`st] 为 [`[*STATE](*this)] 的引用。

[:en] The asynchronous operation is completed by first destroying the coroutine
frame using [`st.[*handle].destroy()] and then invoking [`set_stopped(std::move(st.[*rcvr]))].
[:zh_CN] 异步操作通过首先使用 [`st.[*handle].destroy()] 销毁协程帧，然后调用
[`set_stopped(std::move(st.[*rcvr]))] 来完成。

[para:returns]
[:en] [`noop_coroutine()].
[:zh_CN] [`noop_coroutine()]。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member return_void[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
void return_void();
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:effects]
[:en] Does nothing.
[:zh_CN] 不执行任何操作。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member return_value[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
template<class V>
  void return_value(V&& v);
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:effects]
[:en] Equivalent to [`[*result].emplace(std::forward<V>(v))].
[:zh_CN] 等价于 [`[*result].emplace(std::forward<V>(v))]。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member get_env[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
[[redoc("[=unspec]")]] get_env() const noexcept;
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:returns]
[:en] An object [`env] such that queries are forwarded as follows:
[:zh_CN] 一个对象 [`env]，使得按如下转发查询：
[list]
[item]
[:en] [`env.query(get_start_scheduler)] returns [`start_scheduler_type([*SCHED](*this))].
[:zh_CN] [`env.query(get_start_scheduler)] 返回 [`start_scheduler_type([*SCHED](*this))]。
[item]
[:en] [`env.query(get_allocator)] returns
[`allocator_type(get_allocator(get_env([*RCVR](*this))))]
if this expression is well-formed and [`allocator_type()] otherwise.
[:zh_CN] [`env.query(get_allocator)] 返回
[`allocator_type(get_allocator(get_env([*RCVR](*this))))] 如果该表达式良构，否则
返回 [`allocator_type()]。
[item]
[:en] [`env.query(get_stop_token)] returns [`[*STATE](*this).[*get-stop-token]()].
[:zh_CN] [`env.query(get_stop_token)] 返回 [`[*STATE](*this).[*get-stop-token]()]。
[item]
[:en] For any other query [`q] and arguments [`a...] a call to
[`env.query(q, a...)] returns [`[*STATE](*this)].
[:zh_CN] 对于任意其他查询 [`q] 和实参 [`a...]，[`env.query(q, a...)] 的调用返回 [`[*STATE](*this)]。

[:en] [`[*environment].query(q, a...)] if this expression is well-formed and
[`forwarding_query(q)] is well-formed and is [`true].
[:zh_CN] 如果 [`[*environment].query(q, a...)] 良构，并且 [`forwarding_query(q)]
良构且为 [`true]，则为该表达式。

[:en] Otherwise [`env.query(q, a...)] is ill-formed.
[:zh_CN] 否则 [`env.query(q, a...)] 非良构。
[list:end]
[div:end]

[%@lib@member operator new[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
void* operator new(size_t size);
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:effects]
[:en] Equivalent to: [`return operator new(size, allocator_arg, allocator_type());]
[:zh_CN] 等价于：[`return operator new(size, allocator_arg, allocator_type());]
[div:end]

[%@lib@member operator new[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
template<class Alloc, class... Args>
  void* operator new(size_t size, allocator_arg_t, Alloc alloc, Args&&...);
template<class This, class Alloc, class... Args>
  void* operator new(size_t size, const This&, allocator_arg_t, Alloc alloc, Args&&...);
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para]
[:en] Let [`PAlloc] be [`allocator_traits<Alloc>::template rebind_alloc<U>],
where [`U] is an unspecified type whose size and alignment are both
[`__STDCPP_DEFAULT_NEW_ALIGNMENT__].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`PAlloc] 为 [`allocator_traits<Alloc>::template rebind_alloc<U>]，
其中 [`U] 为未指明的类型，其大小和对齐均为 [`__STDCPP_DEFAULT_NEW_ALIGNMENT__]。

[para:mandates]
[:en] [`allocator_traits<PAlloc>::pointer] is a pointer type.
[:zh_CN] [`allocator_traits<PAlloc>::pointer] 为指针类型。

[para:effects]
[:en] Initializes an allocator [`palloc] of type [`PAlloc] with [`alloc].
[:zh_CN] 以 [`alloc] 初始化 [`PAlloc] 类型的分配器 [`palloc]。

[:en] Uses [`palloc] to allocate storage for the smallest array of [`U]
sufficient to provide storage for a coroutine state of size [`size], and
unspecified additional state necessary to ensure that [`operator delete] can later
deallocate this memory block with an allocator equal to [`palloc].
[:zh_CN] 使用 [`palloc] 为最小的 [`U] 数组分配存储，其大小足以为 [`size] 大小的
协程状态，以及未指明的额外状态提供存储，该状态为确保随后 [`operator delete] 可以
用等于 [`palloc] 的分配器回收这个内存块所必须。

[para:returns]
[:en] A pointer to the allocated storage.
[:zh_CN] 指向所分配存储的指针。
[div:end]

[%@lib@member operator delete[!task::promise_type]]
[codeblock:declaration]
void operator delete(void* pointer, size_t size) noexcept;
[codeblock:end]

[div:description]
[para:expects]
[:en] [`pointer] was returned from an invocation of the above overload
of [`operator new] with a size argument equal to [`size].
[:zh_CN] [`pointer] 是从某次对上述的 [`operator new] 重载，以等于 [`size] 的大小实参
进行的调用返回的。

[para:effects]
[:en] Deallocates the storage pointed to by [`pointer] using an
allocator equal to that used to allocate it.
[:zh_CN] 使用等于分配时所用的分配器，回收 [`pointer] 所指向的存储。
[div:end]
